# GUI Coding Standards

Brandon's lens for psibase frontend code. See canonical examples in
[@packages/shared-ui/lib/query-keys.ts](packages/shared-ui/lib/query-keys.ts),
[@packages/shared-ui/components/form/app-form.tsx](packages/shared-ui/components/form/app-form.tsx),
and [@packages/shared-ui/shadcn/ui](packages/shared-ui/shadcn/ui).

## Share, don't fork
Reach for `@shared-ui` first. Don't duplicate an existing shared schema, hook, component, or helper — import the canonical one and delete the local copy.

## Hide, don't disable
Action controls a user can't legitimately use should not render. UI gating doesn't replace plugin/service-level auth — both must be present.

```tsx
// BAD
<Button disabled={!canEdit} onClick={onEdit}>Edit</Button>

// GOOD
{canEdit && <Button onClick={onEdit}>Edit</Button>}
```

## Surface every state
Loading, empty, error, and "you can't do this because…" states must be explicit and rendered where the user expected to act — not silently absent.

## Click target == visual target
Padding, hover styles, and focus rings belong on the interactive element, not the wrapper.

## URL is the source of truth
Tabs, sub-views, and selection state belong in routes. Read identifiers from `useParams`, not local state. Side menus reflect the current route.

## TanStack Query
- Query keys live in a centralized `queryKeys` object per app (see `@shared-ui/lib/query-keys.ts`) — never inlined.
- Reach the `QueryClient` via the `context` arg of `onSuccess`/`onError`, not by importing it.
- Validate every response with **zod**.
- Prefer one combined query over many small ones hitting the same endpoint on the same page.
- Set explicit `staleTime`s — the default `0` causes refetch storms.

```tsx
// BAD
useQuery({ queryKey: ['user', id], queryFn: () => fetchUser(id) });

// GOOD
useQuery({
  queryKey: queryKeys.user(id),
  queryFn: () => userSchema.parse(await fetchUser(id)),
  staleTime: 30_000,
});
```

## TanStack Form
- Use the shared `useAppForm` (`@shared-ui/components/form/app-form.tsx`) and its bound field/submit components — not hand-rolled state.
- Name the form variable specifically (e.g., `inviteForm`); never `form` (shadows `<form>`).
- One form, one submit handler. Two submit paths mean two forms.
- Reset via `formApi.reset()` inside `onSubmit`, not in a `useEffect`.

## Toasts and errors
- One success toast per user action — don't double-toast from both the hook and the caller.
- Don't swallow promise errors inside `toast.promise(...)` — use `.unwrap()` or a real `onError`.
- Keep toast/copy style (e.g., trailing periods) consistent with neighboring strings.

## TypeScript
- `field?: T` already implies `| undefined`; don't append it.
- Avoid non-null assertions (`!`) — pass values through (e.g., mutation `vars`) so they aren't needed.

## Component & file structure
- Split monolithic components into a directory of focused files; the umbrella composition gets a semantic name.
- Prefer shadcn primitives from `@shared-ui/shadcn/ui` (`Card`, `Skeleton`, `TableCaption`, etc.) over hand-rolled markup.
- A `useEffect` whose only job is to mirror computed values into state is a smell — compute inline.

```tsx
// BAD
const [fullName, setFullName] = useState('');
useEffect(() => setFullName(`${first} ${last}`), [first, last]);

// GOOD
const fullName = `${first} ${last}`;
```

## Dead weight
Delete what's no longer used: imports, dependencies, files orphaned by a refactor, local copies superseded by `@shared-ui`. When removing a shared resource, sweep all consumers in the same change.

## Mechanical vs feature changes
Formatting-only or rename-only edits belong in their own commit. Don't bury feature diffs in mechanical churn.

## Walk the flow
A UI change is also a UX change. Mentally walk it with multiple accounts and roles; handle auth-gated paths, empty data, network errors, expired tokens, and role transitions.
